stions about the contention that socialism has been proven unworkable. He concludes that strengthening the rational capacity of the state may still be the key to improving social and economic justice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362670640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626706423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626706/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles